Practical Photoshop - Issue 77 - August 2017 - True PDF - zeke23
English | 48 pages | True PDF | 12 MB
Our project-based Photoshop training courses will guide you step-by-step through the basic skills you need to:

    Improve your photographs
    Maximize images for web and print
    Build image collages
    Develop creative projects with Photoshop's painting and drawing tools

We authors are all current or former community college instructors, and Adobe Certified Instructors in Adobe Photoshop®. Together, we have taught Photoshop to thousands of students, both in traditional classrooms and online. In our 20+ years of teaching Photoshop, we have learned first hand from our students which Photoshop skills they feel are the most essential, and also which Photoshop techniques they find the most difficult to master. We have used our students’ feedback to determine the topics, their sequence, and the step by step tutorials.

Our Adobe Photoshop training is divided into two courses of hands-on tutorials:

    Practical Photoshop CC 2015, Level 1
    Versions available for both CC 2015 and CC 2015.5!
    Practical Photoshop CC 2015, Level 2

The projects and the theory behind the two course series maps to both a full year's Photoshop instruction at the college level and also to the exam objectives for Adobe's industry-standard certification: Visual Communication with Adobe Photoshop (Adobe Certified Associate). The courses have also been used successfully for high school enrichment and home-schooled students
